# New Beginnings I left her in the evening,
       her touch as cold as a winter's breeze,
she turned to me one last time,
       quick to dispel me of my crimes.
I looked through her eyes,
       never having grasped their weight,
she looked through mine,
       as if to issue a fine.

She was no ordinary girl,
       requiring constant care,
